# Tamil Literature Platform

Version: 1.0
Status: Draft
Document Type: Product Requirements Document (PRD)

---

# Vision

Build the world's best discovery-first platform for Tamil books.

Unlike traditional bookstores that begin with search or categories, this platform presents a personalized literature feed that helps readers discover books through authors, themes, literary movements, publishers, and editorial recommendations.

The platform combines a curated catalog, editorial workflows, knowledge graph, and modern commerce into a single ecosystem.

---

# Goals

## Primary Goals

• Discovery-first reading experience

• High quality editorial catalog

• Publisher self-service onboarding

• Unified catalog across publishers

• Simple commerce experience

• Anonymous personalization

• AI-assisted editorial workflows

• Serverless-first cloud architecture

---

# Non Goals

The platform is not intended to become:

• General ecommerce marketplace

• Social network

• Ebook reader

• Library management software

• ERP

---

# Product Principles

## Discovery over Search

Books should find readers.

Readers should not have to know what they are searching for.

---

## Editorial Quality

Every published book is reviewed by editors.

Publisher imports never publish directly.

---

## Headless Architecture

Frontend, APIs, CMS and Commerce evolve independently.

---

## Open Standards

Avoid vendor lock-in.

Use PostgreSQL.

Use Open APIs.

Infrastructure as Code.

---

## Managed Services

Prefer managed AWS services.

Only run long-lived containers where necessary.

